BekreftelseSendtSøknad.SelvInformere: You must notify and inform your employer yourself about your planned leave.

BekreftelseSendtSøknad.ManglendeDokument: You must send the documentation so we can process your case. You can upload the documentation here under your case. Once received, the prosessing time is usually around 4 to 6 weeks.
BekreftelseSendtSøknad.HuskÅInformere: Remember to inform your employer about the duration of your leave and whether it will be full-time or part-time. Nav does not provide this information to your employer. If you make any changes to your plan, you must also notify your employer.
BekreftelseSendtSøknad.HvisDuVilEndre: If you want to make changes to your plan
BekreftelseSendtSøknad.SendEndringssøkna: If you want to change your parental benefit plan, you can submit a change application by selecting 'Change', available above your plan. Your changes will then be processed by Nav, and you will receive a response with the updated plan.
BekreftelseSendtSøknad.DuFårTidligstSvar: YOU WILL GET THE EARLIEST RESPONSE
BekreftelseSendtSøknad.TidligstSvarForkl: The earliest possible response to your application will be 4 weeks prior to your first day of {erFp, select, true {parental benefit} other {pregnancy benefits}}. Your employer must submit the income report for your application to be prosessed. This is due to our need for the most current income information when calculating what you will receive in {erFp, select, true {parental benefit} other {pregnancy benefits}}.
BekreftelseSendtSøknad.FireUkerFør: Four weeks before your first day of {erFp, select, true {parental benefit} other {pregnancy benefits}}
BekreftelseSendtSøknad.NårDuFårSvar: When will you receive an answer to your application?
BekreftelseSendtSøknad.DuKanTidligstFåSv: You will receive the earliest possible response to your application once all the required documentation has been submitted. We will notify you when your application has been processed, and you can track its status here.
When we have all necessary documentation, the expected processing time is 6 weeks.
BekreftelseSendtSøknad.NårUtbetalesPenge: When will the money be paid?
BekreftelseSendtSøknad.Utbetalingstidspu: You will usually receive the money 1 week after your application is approved.
on Nav's website you can see the payment on the evening of the day the money is paid.
BekreftelseSendtSøknad.VenterPåInntektsm: Your employer must submit an income form to us to tell us about your earnings. We must receive the income form before we can process your application.
If you have multiple employers, they must all send their own income forms.
Your employer has received a notice on nav.no to send the income form.
Your employer will receive a notice on nav.no when they can send the income form.
The income form can be sent earliest four weeks prior to your first day of parental benefit. This is due to our need for the most current income information when calculating your parental benefit.

The income form can be sent earliest four weeks prior to your first day of pregnancy benefits. This is due to our need for the most current income information when calculating your pregnancy benefits.

BruktOpplysningerOmArbeidsforhold.tittel: Nav has retrieved information about your employment
The other parent has applied for parental benefit. For the other parent to receive parental benefit in certain periods, the regulations require that you are active, for example in work. In the application, the other parent has stated that you are working in one or more of these periods.

Nav has therefore retrieved information about your employment from the The State Register of Employers and Employees (the Aa Register). We use this information when we process the other parent’s application. We can also use the information for other periods in future applications. You can check what is registered about you in the AA Register (opens in a new tab).
We have done this under the National Insurance Act § 21-4. You can read more about the processing of personal data (opens in a new tab).
The regulations for activity requirements are in the National Insurance Act § 14-13. If you want to know more, you will find information on nav.no/parental-benefit (opens in a new tab).

beregning.forklaringer.ytelserBareOppTil: Benefits are only calculated up to 6G

If you have a combined income over 6G and have multiple employment relationships, we distribute the income up to this limit. How we distribute the income depends on which combination of incomes you have and whether the employer requires reimbursement from Nav.
